snippet.textDisplay: The Oscars was all over the place and way too random! M&M, a has been rapper performing for who knows why? Maya and Kirstin doing some weird ass number? The whole Cats thing trying to be way too cheeky! I think without a host it felt directionless. I'm so glad Joaquin won! Again we have a Best Picture that maybe twenty people saw! It needs to be tightened down to three hours. Handing out awards to the sound assistant's caterer seems counterintuitive. The Oscars is no longer an awards show but an answer to Hollywood Backlash. If they want it to be more equitable hand out big awards sporadically throughout the show. Bring it back down to five films. Jo Jo Rabbit was good but it definitely was not Best Picture material. And please people if you win an Oscar and you have 30 people up there pick a point person to make your  speech!
